  <shortlink>api xbasic asynchronous function</shortlink>
  <topic>XBASIC_ASYNCHRONOUS Function</topic>
  <description>Run current script asynchronously (after call).</description>
  <syntax>V XBASIC_ASYNCHRONOUS()</syntax>
  <discussion>The XBASIC_ASYNCHRONOUS() function causes the script to wait until after other Alpha Anywhere processes have been completed, not including screen refreshes.</discussion>
  <example code="xb"><![CDATA[' start process
xbasic_asynchronous()
' start another process]]></example>
  <limitations>Desktop applications only.</limitations>
